text:
2-8 Walker Street, on the N.E. corner of West Broadway.

October 10, 1928,

P. L. Sperr.

West Broadway, east side, south from Walker Street. At the left is Sixth Avenue South, an extension that runs to Church Street and upon which are the several buildings shown.

View 2 is limited, confining itself to the foreground structures. The photographer views same in an eastward direction along North Moore Street. Beyond these lofts is the Sixth Avenue and Church Street convergence and at the apex of which is the partially seen New York Telephone Building.
